$ Vim ex command: filetype

{ filetype on #vim-filetype-on

code {
filetype on
code }

  `filetype on` does basically a `runtime filetype.vim` (thus, it runs → development/vim/runtime/filetype_vim[`$VIMRUNTIME/filetype.vim`].

   When vim is running with a GUI, it also source → development/vim/sources/runtime/menu_vim


}
{ filetype indent on #vim-filetype-indent-on

? `:filetype indent on` seems to indirectly set → development/vim/options/indentexpr[`indentexpr`].

}


sa:

  The → development/vim/runtime/ftplugin[`ftplugin/`] runtime directory.

  → development/vim/commands[Ex commands]
